      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "PEXA (Property Exchange Australia) is the national electronic settlement platform that replaced paper-based property settlement in Queensland. On settlement day, your solicitor uses PEXA to lodge the title transfer documents and receive the purchase funds electronically. Sellers do not attend settlement in person and typically receive funds in their nominated account within a few hours of settlement completing."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does PEXA settlement take in Queensland?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "PEXA settlement itself is near-instant once all parties are ready. The buyer's lender releases funds electronically, the title is transferred, and the seller's solicitor distributes proceeds the same day. Sellers typically see funds in their account within one to three hours of the scheduled settlement time, compared to manual settlement which could take until end of business day or even the following morning."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What can go wrong with PEXA electronic settlement?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
